Did my husband leave early?


78
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,549
Yes, at around 8 a.m.
He said he had plans for the morning.


79
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:43,549
And the police keep calling,
saying they need your statement.


80
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,650
What should I tell them?


81
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,520
Come up with an excuse
and ignore their calls.


82
00:08:46,690 --> 00:08:48,620
We shouldn't have to worry
about things like that.


83
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:53,730
My gosh, seriously?


84
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:55,600
This is making me feel so uneasy.


85
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:58,330
My young son is the only male
in the house.


86
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:03,100
Maybe we should really move
to a different area.


87
00:09:03,970 --> 00:09:04,910
Right.


88
00:09:04,970 --> 00:09:07,110
Okay. I'll see you later at the school.


89
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:11,510
Right. That's why you need
to send all the investment funds


90
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:14,280
to their account
and consolidate them as soon as you can.


91
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,850
We need to buy as much time as possible.


92
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:19,290
Ask Mr. Jung for more time.


93
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:21,990
I'll go there now
and try to negotiate myself.


94
00:09:22,460 --> 00:09:24,330
Okay, thanks. Talk to you later.


95
00:09:31,970 --> 00:09:35,300
Is something going on at work?


96
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,570
There's always something going on.


97
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:41,840
-But you don't need to worry.
-Okay.


98
00:09:44,380 --> 00:09:47,720
I heard someone smashed a window
at our next-door neighbor's last night.


99
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:49,820
But it doesn't even worry you, does it?


100
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,550
Why should I be worried?


101
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:55,520
Even if someone broke in, they'd run away
the moment they saw your bare face.


102
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:56,620
What?


103
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:58,330
What are you talking about?


104
00:09:58,390 --> 00:10:00,800
Don't forget that I participated
in the Miss Korea pageant.


105
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:02,260
My beauty is officially acknowledged!


106
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:05,230
You know, young girls these days
are not even recognizable


107
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,670
without the smartphone filters
and their makeup.


108
00:10:07,770 --> 00:10:10,140
When it comes to looks,
I'm in the top one percent.


109
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:13,240
Well, maybe two.
Yes, in the top two percent.


110
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,180
Hello?


111
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:20,310
Yes, speaking. Who is this?


112
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,420
The police?


113
00:10:26,490 --> 00:10:27,720
What is this about?


114
00:10:28,590 --> 00:10:29,720
Sorry?


115
00:10:31,490 --> 00:10:33,690
I see. Just a moment, please.


116
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:14,800
Mom!


117
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:30,620
Son, wake up. The sun's up.


118
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,360
Wake up, Yi-chan.


119
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:36,690
An Yi-chan!


120
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,360
Yi-chan.


121
00:11:39,190 --> 00:11:41,430
What's wrong? Yi-chan.


122
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:44,000
Look at Mom, Yi-chan.


123
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:45,570
Are you not feeling well?


124
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,840
Answer me.


125
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,700
An Yi-chan.


126
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:54,280
Yi-chan, answer me. Yi-chan!


127
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,780
What's wrong, Yi-chan?


128
00:11:56,310 --> 00:11:57,380
Yi-chan.


129
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,050
My gosh.


130
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,720
All right, kids.
Let's do some stretching. Get up.


131
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:04,950
-Okay!
-Okay!


132
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:09,890
Hold on. Is Yi-chan not here yet?


133
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:11,230
He's missing school today.


134
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:13,090
He's sick.
I heard he went to see a doctor.


135
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:15,700
-What's wrong with him?
-We have no idea.


136
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,170
That stupid idiot got sick.
He's so annoying.


137
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:19,800
He got sick because he's weak.


138
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,670
He should've exercised regularly.


139
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:30,140
[MRI Safety Precautions]


140
00:12:30,810 --> 00:12:32,950
There's nothing wrong with his brain.


141
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:36,380
You said there was no external injury,
so I think it's just temporary.


142
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:40,860
Was he shocked or stressed out
about something by any chance?


143
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,760
Something did happen at home.


144
00:12:44,730 --> 00:12:46,130
This can happen to kids


145
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:48,930
after suffering
from a huge emotional shock or stress,


146
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,560
so that could be what triggered this.


147
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,170
How long will it last?


148
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,570
I can't give you an exact answer.


149
00:12:55,970 --> 00:12:58,870
In some cases,
the symptom suddenly goes away.


150
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:00,980
But I've also seen cases
where it lasts quite a while.


151
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:06,710
For now, let's try art therapy


152
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:09,350
coupled with speech therapy
and see how that goes.


153
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:12,450
Our priority should be creating
a stress-free environment for him


154
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:15,290
so we can help him
regain psychological stability.


155
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:17,760
Okay.


156
00:13:21,830 --> 00:13:25,130
[Doctor's Office]


157
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,870
[Doctor's Office 1]


158
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,940
What happened?


159
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,500
Where is Yi-chan?


160
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,910
They're still running some tests on him.


161
00:13:33,170 --> 00:13:35,480
I think he's in shock
because of what happened last night.


162
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:37,040
He can't speak.


163
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:42,550
The doctor says it's temporary,
but I don't know what will happen.


164
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,560
Don't worry too much.


165
00:13:52,330 --> 00:13:53,990
He'll recover soon,


166
00:13:54,130 --> 00:13:56,430
as if nothing happened.


167
00:13:58,230 --> 00:13:59,300
You think so?


168
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:02,640
I think it was when I was about seven.


169
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,710
I suddenly couldn't speak


170
00:14:06,070 --> 00:14:08,840
when my dog died unexpectedly.


171
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:11,810
I think it lasted about a month or so,


172
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:13,350
if my memory serves me correctly.


173
00:14:13,810 --> 00:14:14,880
Really?


174
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:16,350
Yes. And look at me now.


175
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,490
As you can see, I'm totally fine.


176
00:14:18,590 --> 00:14:20,190
I'm so healthy.


177
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:24,960
Yi-chan will be fine too.


178
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:27,500
I really hope so.


179
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:32,430
I'm not surprised though
because it must've been so hard for him.


180
00:14:33,230 --> 00:14:34,940
After what happened to his dad,


181
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,100
he had to go through all that
at his new school.


182
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,980
And with his mom
going in and out of the police station...


183
00:14:45,610 --> 00:14:48,350
With what happened last night


184
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:51,620
and now this too...
Did you get any sleep last night?


185
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:53,850
It's fine.


186
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:55,920
You know that I'm always full of energy.


187
00:14:55,990 --> 00:14:59,590
How can you always be full of energy?
You're not a robot.


188
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:03,700
I'll stay here. Why don't you


189
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,170
get some rest?


190
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:06,870
No, it's okay.


191
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,540
My gosh. I shouldn't be out here chatting.


192
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,010
The tests will be done soon.


193
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:13,340
I should go check.


194
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,640
Wait.


195
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,210
It's okay, Song Yeo-wool.


196
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:48,980
Don't cry. Everything will be okay.


197
00:15:50,380 --> 00:15:51,580
You can't cry.


