00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,630
Is that also an adult thing?


260
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,830
Yes, it is.


261
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:57,480
So your most memorable moment
on Jeju Island was the beach.


262
00:21:58,610 --> 00:22:00,510
Did you have fun back then?


263
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:06,150
This must be you, Yi-chan.


264
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:08,960
Who's this? Your mom?


265
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:15,300
I don't drink canned coffee.


266
00:22:17,630 --> 00:22:20,530
Why did you want to see me?


267
00:22:22,870 --> 00:22:24,200
Ms. Cha Do-yeong.


268
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:27,540
I heard you were with Chef Jung Mi-do


269
00:22:27,610 --> 00:22:30,040
on the night of the concert.


270
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:32,850
Were you with him the whole night?


271
00:22:33,210 --> 00:22:35,180
Well...


272
00:22:36,020 --> 00:22:38,150
I don't really remember.


273
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:42,220
It was hectic because of the blackout.


274
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:46,290
And I wasn't alone with him.
My husband was there too.


275
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,000
What's your relationship
with Chef Jung Mi-do?


276
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:54,840
Well... My husband invested a share
in Chef Jung's restaurant.


277
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:57,870
And I'm managing it with him
as the co-owner.


278
00:22:58,310 --> 00:22:59,410
Is that everything?


279
00:23:00,510 --> 00:23:03,640
What else could there be?


280
00:23:04,580 --> 00:23:06,510
By the way...


281
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:08,550
Why are you asking me this?


282
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:10,050
That night,


283
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,790
Jung Mi-do turned down
the school's circuit breaker.


284
00:23:12,850 --> 00:23:15,190
Did you find anything strange
about him that day?


285
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:16,320
Mi-do--


286
00:23:17,190 --> 00:23:19,490
No, Chef Jung did? My gosh.


287
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:22,260
Do you know anything about


288
00:23:22,330 --> 00:23:25,000
Chairman Doh Jin-sol
and Chef Jung Mi-do's relationship?


289
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:27,830
There's no way he would've done that.


290
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:30,140
I clearly saw them going into the hotel--


291
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:36,840
What I meant was,
he's not someone who would've done that.


292
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:42,820
I heard he was pursuing a new partnership


293
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:44,380
with Chairman Doh Jin-sol


294
00:23:44,450 --> 00:23:46,950
regarding the restaurant's investment
and trademark registration.


295
00:23:47,620 --> 00:23:48,720
Didn't you know?


296
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:51,460
What a total jerk.


297
00:23:51,690 --> 00:23:54,490
Anyway, he has nothing to do with me.


298
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,930
I'm completely done with him.


299
00:23:58,430 --> 00:24:00,730
That means you admit
you had a personal relationship with him


300
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:02,900
apart from a business one, right?


301
00:24:02,970 --> 00:24:04,000
What?


302
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:07,470
Well... That's not what I meant.


303
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,820
I won't comment on that.


304
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:19,720
Mi-ran's law. Don't you know Mi-ran's law?


305
00:24:20,090 --> 00:24:24,190
Mi-ran was investigated so unfairly


306
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:25,860
by people like you.


307
00:24:27,190 --> 00:24:28,960
You thought I didn't know, right?


308
00:24:29,130 --> 00:24:32,330
I have nothing to do on Jeju Island,
so I watch the news a lot.


309
00:24:33,230 --> 00:24:37,170
Anyway, I won't utter a word
until my lawyer comes.


310
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,240
So don't try to feel me out.


311
00:24:51,850 --> 00:24:54,620
I'm Ms. Cha Do-yeong's lawyer.
You can speak to me.


312
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:01,560
You never miss out on anything.


313
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:04,560
Ms. Song,


314
00:25:04,630 --> 00:25:07,730
this detective tried to feel me out
by bombarding me with questions.


315
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:11,300
I have nothing more to say,


316
00:25:11,370 --> 00:25:14,010
so finish talking with my lawyer.


317
00:25:14,070 --> 00:25:16,380
-I leave the rest to you. Good luck!
-Right.


318
00:25:30,690 --> 00:25:35,960
[Interview Room]


319
00:25:32,490 --> 00:25:34,960
Aren't you going too far


320
00:25:35,030 --> 00:25:36,400
by defending an unfaithful actress?


321
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:39,200
It's simply her private life
unrelated to the case.


322
00:25:39,870 --> 00:25:42,540
Stop crossing the line
under the pretext of the investigation.


323
00:25:43,370 --> 00:25:48,040
I'll decide whether it ends
as a private matter or leads to the crime.


324
00:25:54,980 --> 00:25:57,580
Hey. Are you done questioning the helper?


325
00:25:58,020 --> 00:25:59,350
What was her motive?


326
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:01,960
She's keeping her mouth shut.


327
00:26:02,090 --> 00:26:03,490
I couldn't even get to the motive.


328
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:07,860
All I got out of her was
that she has no family or friends here.


329
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:10,860
My goodness.


330
00:26:10,930 --> 00:26:14,400
As long as she keeps her mouth shut,
what can we possibly do?


331
00:26:15,670 --> 00:26:17,000
This wasn't her first offense either.


332
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:18,540
It wasn't?


333
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:21,370
Ms. Sim Ae-soon has been convicted
of arson and murder.


334
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:22,710
Arson and murder?


335
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:25,010
Who did she murder?


336
00:26:24,710 --> 00:26:26,610
[Police Station]


337
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:26,180
Her husband.


338
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:28,620
Twenty years ago, she was arrested
for murdering her husband


339
00:26:28,350 --> 00:26:32,420
[Police Station]


340
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,280
and setting fire to her house.


341
00:26:31,890 --> 00:26:34,650
[Murder and arson are serious crimes.]


342
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,260
[She served 15 years and was on parole.]


343
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:40,530
[Her then 12-year-old daughter
seems to have run away from home.]


344
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:42,460
[She hasn't heard from her since.]


345
00:26:44,260 --> 00:26:46,130
Then could that lady be...


346
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,880
Is this a bad time?


347
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:58,580
No, it's fine. Come in.


348
00:27:05,650 --> 00:27:06,990
How's Yi-chan?


349
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,460
His tests are normal.


350
00:27:09,790 --> 00:27:11,290
He started art therapy.


351
00:27:11,460 --> 00:27:14,930
He'll have to take it easy
for the time being.


352
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:18,200
That means we're not moving just yet.


353
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,870
-Does that mean--
-Our contract


354
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:22,640
remains valid too.


355
00:27:24,170 --> 00:27:26,010
Sounds good to me.


356
00:27:26,170 --> 00:27:27,870
As long as my client needs me.


357
00:27:28,940 --> 00:27:30,380
Speaking of which,


358
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:33,580
could you look into the house helper,
Ms. Sim Ae-soon, for me?


359
00:27:33,650 --> 00:27:35,050
Why? What about her?


360
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:36,620
I thought everything was over.


361
00:27:37,050 --> 00:27:40,390
I don't believe she did such a thing
just because she disliked me.


362
00:27:41,150 --> 00:27:42,460
Something feels off.


363
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:46,260
In addition, she's been convicted
of murder and arson 20 years ago.


364
00:27:46,330 --> 00:27:47,760
Murder and arson?


365
00:27:51,460 --> 00:27:52,630
I see.


366
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:54,930
All right.


367
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:59,570
By the way, I'm on my way
to the police station.


368
00:27:59,770 --> 00:28:01,110
I guess it's my turn now.


369
00:28:03,140 --> 00:28:04,080
Be careful.


370
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,550
I'm sure everything will be all right.


371
00:28:05,610 --> 00:28:07,080
I'm just being summoned as a witness.


372
00:28:07,150 --> 00:28:10,380
If the detective wants to see me,
I should come right over, shouldn't I?


373
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:13,590
Still, that detective can be
quite persistent.


374
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:16,890
Come on. This isn't my first time.


375
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,990
I know how to handle these situations.


376
00:28:19,460 --> 00:28:20,490
Goodness.


377
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:22,960
Anyway, I'm off.


378
00:28:34,970 --> 00:28:37,210
[Death Registration Form
Name: An Ji-yong]


379
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,980
[Name of Informant: Song Yeo-wool]


380
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,900
I heard about what happened at your house.


381
00:29:04,870 --> 00:29:06,640
How's Yi-chan doing?


382
00:29:07,140 --> 00:29:09,910
Since when are we concerned
about each other?


383
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:12,080
Will you leave me alone for a while?


384
00:29:12,410 --> 00:29:14,180
I already have enough on my plate.


385
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:21,150
It's a settlement agreement.


386
00:29:24,460 --> 00:29:25,730
Why are you doing this?


387
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:29,300
In return, I'd like you to help the helper


388
00:29:29,730 --> 00:29:30,960
who damaged your house.


389
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:33,600
What do you care about that lady?


390
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:35,670
Do you know her?


391
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:41,170
I know what it is like
to have no one to turn to.


392
00:29:43,410 --> 00:29:45,150
You're a competent lawyer, aren't you?


393
00:29:45,210 --> 00:29:46,680
Are you sure that's all?


394
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,920
What are you up to now?


395
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,760
I take it you don't want to settle?


396
00:30:03,060 --> 00:30:04,600
"Danny Oh."


397
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:07,870
"A member of the ice hockey team
at the University of Toronto, Canada."


398
00:30:07,930 --> 00:30:10,370
"A member of Toronto Thunders
Ice Hockey Club."


399
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:14,140
-Are you a Korean-Canadian?
-Yes, I am.


400
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:16,180
Why did you come all the way here
to Jeju Island?


401
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:20,680
My ligament got torn to pieces,


402
00:30:20,750 --> 00:30:23,520
so I couldn't continue
as a professional ice hockey player.


403
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:27,150
I had to make a living, but ice hockey
was the only thing I'd ever done.


404
00:30:27,250 --> 00:30:28,560
Just then,


405
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:31,090
I heard that this school had an opening.


406
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:32,730
I thought, "Why not?"


407
00:30:32,990 --> 00:30:35,230
Also... It's Jeju Island.


408
00:30:35,330 --> 00:30:36,900
How nice.


409
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,030
I see.


410
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:43,070
In the chairman's office,


411
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,710
we found your letter of resignation.


412
00:30:45,470 --> 00:30:46,540
[Letter of Resignation]


413
00:30:46,110 --> 00:30:48,010
Submitted on the day of her death.


414
00:30:48,370 --> 00:30:49,440
What happened?


415
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:50,880
Oh, this?


416
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:51,740
[Evidence, Collected on October 2, 2021,
in the chairman's office]


417
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:54,380
I changed my mind.


418
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:58,550
Luckily, the chairman
rejected my letter of resignation.


419
00:30:59,950 --> 00:31:01,220
You changed your mind?


420
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:07,460
No matter how I look at it,


421
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:11,500
you two don't look like
just a teacher and a parent.


422
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:13,630
Then what do we look like?


423
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:17,000
Did Ms. Song ask you for help


424
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:18,640
regarding the chairman?


425
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:19,870
What does that even mean?


426
00:31:19,940 --> 00:31:21,880
Was your letter of resignation rejected


427
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:23,640
because of Ms. Song?


428
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:26,150
My gosh.


429
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:30,550
Are all detectives so prejudiced?


430
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:33,750
Sir, no matter how difficult it is
to meet women around here,


431
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:36,120
me and this lady?


432
00:31:36,420 --> 00:31:38,390
I'm more popular than you think.


433
00:31:39,260 --> 00:31:40,790
She's no ordinary lady.


434
00:31:41,030 --> 00:31:43,600
Two people around her have died already.


435
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:44,800
So what?


436
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,870
I know you two are
hiding something from me.


437
00:31:51,170 --> 00:31:54,010
I advise you to tell the truth
and cooperate.


438
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,010
I don't know what you're talking about.


439
00:31:59,010 --> 00:32:00,080
Wait.


440
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,120
I didn't realize how late it was.


441
00:32:04,420 --> 00:32:06,390
If we're done here,


442
00:32:06,450 --> 00:32:09,120
I'll be going now. I'm quite busy.


443
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:12,760
Also, if you keep threatening me
like this,


444
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:17,460
I'll file an official complaint
through the embassy.


445
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:20,000
You know, I'm a Canadian citizen.


446
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,330
Bye.


447
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:24,670
Gosh.


448
00:32:26,540 --> 00:32:27,570
Oh, well.


449
00:32:31,780 --> 00:32:33,380
Are you done? What did he say?


450
00:32:33,610 --> 00:32:34,810
-Detective Choi.
-Yes?


451
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,780
Run a background check on that punk.


452
00:32:36,850 --> 00:32:37,880
Yes, sir.


453
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:39,990
Unbelievable.


454
00:32:47,190 --> 00:32:50,800
The funeral is over now.
I think it's time to put an end to things.


455
00:32:52,230 --> 00:32:54,870
I'd like to hear your opinion, Mr. Cormer.


456
00:32:55,340 --> 00:32:56,670
My opinion?


457
00:32:57,670 --> 00:32:59,810
I've already checked with Hong Kong.


458
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,440
You knew everything, didn't you?


459
00:33:04,610 --> 00:33:07,350
I feel bad saying this
about a deceased person,


460
00:33:07,650 --> 00:33:09,480
but how could a woman like her


461
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:12,290
become the chairman of this school?


462
00:33:15,420 --> 00:33:18,690
Whose side are you on now?


463
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:20,630
I never follow people.


464
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:25,630
I just follow the money, as you know.


465
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,470
Unless,


466
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:30,800
you're making me an offer.


467
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:39,310
There's no need to get impatient.


468
00:33:40,510 --> 00:33:43,050
Soon the board will elect


469
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:44,950
the next chairman.


470
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,520
Once the foreign investors


471
00:33:47,590 --> 00:33:49,660
take over management as planned,


472
00:33:50,460 --> 00:33:53,690
you'll be able to recover all your losses.


473
00:33:54,790 --> 00:33:56,300
What about Song Yeo-wool?


474
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,570
Once Mr. An's will
and the lawsuit with the foundation


475
00:34:01,630 --> 00:34:04,600
for compensation are settled,


476
00:34:04,870 --> 00:34:06,240
she'll leave this place.


477
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:09,409
You make it sound so simple.


478
00:34:10,110 --> 00:34:12,310
I'll be away for two weeks.


479
00:34:13,380 --> 00:34:15,520
Sort everything out until I get back.


480
00:34:20,949 --> 00:34:22,360
Anyway, who is it going to be?


481
00:34:22,820 --> 00:34:24,060
The new chairman.


